Name: Hiscores! Gold
About the game: 'Adorable' - Jim Sterling 'There for you to enjoy' - Jim Sterling 'Funny' - Jim Sterling 'Brilliant' - Jim Sterling This... is Hiscores! Gold. A premium re-imagining of a previous AIU game, with just a few small differences: a nice big gold button to press and a pleasing 'cha-ching' sound effect every 100 points. Everything is deliberate. Gameplay has been stripped down to the basic elements - interact with the button, observe your score score increase, but don't dither too long or you'll reset to zero. Purity of esscence. I believe this pure game is worth nearly $200. Who are you to tell me otherwise? (actually I made the game more accessible for poors because I'm nice like that)
